G'day, Here in Northern NSW Australia, last year we missed out on 34% of our annual Average Rainfall (calculated for the previous 15 years)...; so far this year the Accumulated Rainfall is tracking 40% down on the aforementioned Average. During August this year I had 6.4 mm of Rain & 1.4mm of Dew fot 7.8mm of total Precipitation...; and on the 1.5 Acres of Bushfire Fuelbomb surrounding my Hut..., I've put 50 Tons of Water out through my Firehose over the past month, at $20/Ton, trucked in here at ten Tons per Truckload... So all-up I've put 8.3 mm of Water ("33 Points") onto the 1.5 Acres in the muddle of which I live. Firefighting Practice, at night, under Head-Torch ; learning my Hose-Runs..., and trying to soak some Water into the Soil. Tomorrow..., the 6th Truckload of Water arrives, and then I'll be sitting on 15 Tons in my Tanks & twice the Soil Moisture of the surrounding Fuelbomb (40 Tons of Dry Fuel per Hectare /17.5 Tons per Acre). And, Australia is now IMPORTING Wheat, from Canada.... Also, here there are now no Flying Insects to clean off Car Windscreens after driving up the Highway, there are almost no Flies nor Ants either, and last year 90% of all the Fish in our Inland Rivers & Lakes & Dams died from the Heat & low Water-Levels, with the rest of them expected to be dead by the New Year. It rather looks as if Global Warming has already won, actually ; and only the Idiots who choose to think that "Growing the EcoGnomie" actually matters...; have failed to notice that fact. Such is Life... Have a good one. Ciao !
